# CHAPTER 30 — APHEX-X1-SBN

**Serial:** PI220-391-APHEX-X1SBN-2026**

**Classification:** Stage-Based Node Vertical Transport Network

---

## Executive Overview

APHEX-X1-SBN (Stage-Based Network) represents the second evolutionary stage of APHEX-X1.

Rather than relying on a single propulsion architecture throughout the entire building height, APHEX-X1-SBN transforms every floor into an independent propulsion and safety node.

This creates a distributed vertical transportation network.

---

## 1. Core Philosophy

Traditional Elevator:

```text
Machine Room
       ↓
Entire Shaft
```

APHEX-X1-SBN:

```text
Floor Node 1
      ↓
Floor Node 2
      ↓
Floor Node 3
      ↓
Floor Node N
```

Every floor becomes an active participant.

---

## 2. Distributed Node Architecture

Each floor contains:

### Hydraulic Propulsion Block

Provides localized motion.

### Arrest Lock System

Provides safety protection.

### Pressure Management Module

Controls force allocation.

### Synchronization Controller

Coordinates neighboring nodes.

---

## 3. Transportation Sequence

```text
Passenger Detection
         ↓
Mass Calculation
         ↓
Node Force Allocation
         ↓
Floor Block Activation
         ↓
Movement To Adjacent Node
         ↓
Floor Lock Engagement
         ↓
Structural Load Transfer
         ↓
Next Node Activation
```

---

## 4. Distributed Pressure Network

Instead of one large pressure source:

```text
Node A
Node B
Node C
Node D
```

Each contributes only the force required for its section.

Benefits:

* Reduced peak pressure
* Reduced component stress
* Increased redundancy
* Improved efficiency

---

## 5. Multi-Layer Safety Architecture

Protection layers:

### Electromagnetic Rail Locks

### Floor Arrest Modules

### Hydraulic Isolation Valves

### Pressure Containment Systems

### AI Fault Prediction

Each floor can independently secure the system.

---

## 6. Node Isolation Capability

If a node experiences failure:

```text
Node Failure
      ↓
Isolation
      ↓
Bypass Routing
      ↓
Continued Operation
```

This dramatically improves availability.

---

## 7. Regenerative Energy Architecture

Every floor becomes an energy-recovery node.

Benefits:

